x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Until yesterday, ev=
en for a meaningful number of Capitol Hill insiders, former congressman <b>=
Tim Walz </b>was not exactly a known quantity on the national stage. Of cou=
rse, now that <b>Kamala Harris </b>has selected the amiable everyman govern=
or from Minnesota as her running mate, Walz has become, overnight, one of t=
he most scrutinized public figures in America. So far, he=E2=80=99s met the=
 moment, offering up a folksy but smartly honed speech on Tuesday night, al=
ongside Harris, in which he deftly skewered his political foil, <b>J.D. Van=
ce</b>. <br/><br/>In this conversation, adapted from Puck=E2=80=99s daily <=
i>The Powers That Be </i>podcast, <b>Peter Hamby </b>and <b>John Heilemann<=
/b> chew over the most pertinent questions surrounding Walz: Where the hell=
 did he come from, what does he <i>really </i>add to the ticket, what the p=
ick really says about Harris
and her campaign strategy, and much more=E2=80=A6<br/></td>
